Honest question: why do we spend money on helping displaced people from any country? I understand throwing our economic power around to secure airfields and ports of call for our ships. Apart from that, I don’t understand any form of foreign aid. Wasted tax payer dollars. We are not the nanny of the world. We have our own problems. Shut down our borders and stop taking money from poor Americans to send to wealthy people in poor nations.

This is not me saying we should not provide material aid to Israel. As time goes on though we must come to the reality that our resources are finite and we must be prepared to defend ourselves and make ourselves a prosperous nation again. We are spread thin and our economy is in dire straits, dark days on the horizon. It's all about global reserve currency status and the leverage / soft power it provides. Globalists want us weak, dependent, and loyal to the regime that is coming. Who is behind this plot? Is it multiple groups and nations or is there a central driver of all of it?
